				<_option value="useMetric">Use Metric Module</_option>
			</param>
			<param name="pitch"     type="float"   min="0.1"  max="10000.0"	precision="5"	_gui-text="Circular pitch / Metric Module">20.0</param>
			<param name="module"    type="float"   min="0.1"  max="1000.0"	precision="4"   _gui-text="Metric Module instead of CP">1.25</param>
			<_param name="help" type="description">---------------</_param>
			<param name="angle"     type="float"   min="5.0"  max="45.0"   	precision="5"	_gui-text="Pressure angle (5..45)">20.0</param>
			<param name="clearance" type="float"   _gui-text="Clearance" min="0" max="100" precision="5">0</param>
			<_param name="help" type="description">Clearance between bottom of gap of this gear and top of tooth of another</_param>
			<param name="units" type="enum" _gui-text="Units:">
				<item value="1">px</item>
				<item value="3.5433070866">mm</item>
				<item value="90">in</item>
				<item value="1.25">pt</item>
			</param>
			<param name="annotation" type="boolean" _gui-text="Draw annotation text">false</param>
		</page>	
		
   		<page name='advanced' _gui-text='Advanced options'>
			<param name="mount-hole"		type="float" min="0.01"    max="100"	precision="5"	_gui-text="Mount hole diameter">5</param>
			<param name="holes-count"		type="int"   min="0"    max="100"	_gui-text="Number of holes">3</param>
			<param name="holes-border"		type="float" min="1"    max="1000"	precision="5"	_gui-text="Holes border width">5</param>
			<param name="mount_radius"		type="float" min="1"    max="1000"	precision="5"	_gui-text="Mount support diameter">15</param>
                        <!-- unused parameter
			<param name="holes-rounding"	type="float" min="0"    max="1000"	precision="5"	_gui-text="Holes rounding">5</param>
                        -->
			<param name="centercross" type="boolean" _gui-text="Draw center cross">false</param>
			<param name="pitchcircle" type="boolean" _gui-text="Draw pitch circle (for meshing)">false</param>
			<param name="accuracy" type="enum" _gui-text="Tooth Accuracy:">
				<item value="0">automatic</item>
				<item value="20">best: 20 points</item>
				<item value="12">medium: 12 points</item>
				<item value="6">low: 6 points</item>
			</param>
			<_param name="help" type="description">Good accuracy is important with a low tooth count</_param>
		</page>
		<page name='rack' _gui-text='Rack'>
			<param name="drawrack" type="boolean" _gui-text="Draw Rack">false</param>
			<param name="teeth_length" type="int"   min="1"   max="500" _gui-text="Rack Length">10</param>
			<param name="base_height"  type="float" min="0.1" max="100"	precision="4"	_gui-text="Height of Base">5</param>
			<param name="base_tab"     type="float" min="0.1" max="100"	precision="4"	_gui-text="Length of end tab">5</param>
			<_param name="help" type="description">Length (in teeth) of rack.</_param>
			<_param name="packing" type="description">
			.
			
			
			</_param>
		</page>
		<page name="Usage" _gui-text="Usage">
			<_param name="gearuse" type="description" xml:space="preserve">Gears:
Essential to the correct meshing of gears is the notion that the size of the teeth on each gear must be the same.
This is why Circular Pitch(inches)or Module (metric) is used to define gears, rather than say radius.

One measure of size is the Circular Pitch, p, the distance between adjacent teeth around the Pitch Circle.
Thus  p = pi*D/z   where z is the number of teeth on a gear of pitch diameter D.
The SI measure of size is the Module:  m = p/pi = D/z
 
So the apparent diameter changes based on the number of teeth and the Circular Pitch/Module.
	Inches: Circular Pitch is the increment of the Pitch Circle circumference per tooth in inches.
	Metric: Module is the Teeth per millimetre of the Pitch Circle Diameter.
Where:
	Pitch Circle: Radius of this circle is equal to the distance from the center of the gear to the pitch point.
	Pitch Point:  The point of tangency of the pitch circles of two meshing gears.

Pressure angles are in degrees. Usually - 14.5(historical), 20(common), 25.
The higher the pitch angle, the more effort to turn the gear.
		</_param>
		</page>
	</param>	

	<effect>
	<object-type>all</object-type>
		<effects-menu>
			<submenu _name="Render"/>
		</effects-menu>						    		
	</effect>
	<script>
		<command reldir="extensions" interpreter="python">gears-dev.py</command>
	</script>
</inkscape-extension>
